  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The Learning Solution Design must describe in detail the &quot;look and feel&quot; of the training solution, as well as how the&#xD;
    content is organized and presented. Once approved, the Learning Solution Design provides information and structure for&#xD;
    Information developers, who will use the information provided here, as well as information from subject matter experts&#xD;
    and existing documentation, to produce the course.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    All parties who have a direct interest in this training should review this document. This ensures that a common vision&#xD;
    is shared as the engagement progresses from the design to production.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <keyConsiderations xsi:nil="true"/>
  <purpose>&lt;p>&#xD;
    This Learning Solution Design work product serves two main goals:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        It serves as a tool for reaching consensus between the&amp;nbsp;sponsor and the development team&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        It serves as a &quot;road map&quot; for developers as they create the learning materials&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></purpose>
  <impactOfNotHaving xsi:nil="true"/>
  <reasonsForNotNeeding>This is a necessary work product in all engagements developing education and training materials.</reasonsForNotNeeding>
